An environmental agency needs to hire a number of new employees to monitor water and air pollution. The following conditions must be met:- 85 of the new employees will be able to monitor water pollution- 73 of the new employees will be able to monitor air pollution- Exactly 27 of the new employees will be able to monitor both water and air pollution (these 27 are included in the 85 and 73 mentioned above)The problem is to determine the minimum number of employees that need to be hired to fulfill these requirements.The Venn diagram representing the problem is as follows: egin{tikzpicture}    \draw (0,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Water};    \draw (1.5,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Air};    
ode at (0.75,0) {27};    
ode at (-0.8,0) {$85-27$};    
ode at (2.3,0) {$73-27$};\end{tikzpicture}
